{
  "version": 1,
  "voice": "Flo",
  "locale": "en-GB",
  "clips": [
    {
      "id": "guide-b9e6e83",
      "text": "First, let’s learn what a prefix is.",
      "kind": "guide",
      "path": "/audio/narration/guide-b9e6e83.m4a"
    },
    {
      "id": "guide-1bc4cc63",
      "text": "Prefixes are a group of letters that change the meaning of a word when they are added to the start. Most prefixes mean a similar thing when they’re added to different words.",
      "kind": "guide",
      "path": "/audio/narration/guide-1bc4cc63.m4a"
    },
    {
      "id": "guide-752501ec",
      "text": "Today’s prefix is un-.",
      "kind": "guide",
      "path": "/audio/narration/guide-752501ec.m4a"
    },
    {
      "id": "guide-2812bbd7",
      "text": "un- is always spelled u-n. It goes at the start of a base word. un- can mean not, or it can reverse an action. The base word keeps every letter.",
      "kind": "guide",
      "path": "/audio/narration/guide-2812bbd7.m4a"
    },
    {
      "id": "guide-aecba832",
      "text": "These are the words we will explore today.",
      "kind": "guide",
      "path": "/audio/narration/guide-aecba832.m4a"
    },
    {
      "id": "guide-37979160",
      "text": "Today we will review unfair, unkind, unlock, and untidy. Look for un- at the start and notice what it does to each base word.",
      "kind": "guide",
      "path": "/audio/narration/guide-37979160.m4a"
    },
    {
      "id": "guide-438b7c0c",
      "text": "This piece can change the word.",
      "kind": "guide",
      "path": "/audio/narration/guide-438b7c0c.m4a"
    },
    {
      "id": "guide-87bba5d3",
      "text": "Try the same piece with kind.",
      "kind": "guide",
      "path": "/audio/narration/guide-87bba5d3.m4a"
    },
    {
      "id": "guide-8451cfe9",
      "text": "What happens when it meets lock?",
      "kind": "guide",
      "path": "/audio/narration/guide-8451cfe9.m4a"
    },
    {
      "id": "guide-289bc35c",
      "text": "What happens when it meets tidy?",
      "kind": "guide",
      "path": "/audio/narration/guide-289bc35c.m4a"
    },
    {
      "id": "guide-2098076d",
      "text": "Find the prefix at the start of unhappy.",
      "kind": "guide",
      "path": "/audio/narration/guide-2098076d.m4a"
    },
    {
      "id": "guide-514d8c08",
      "text": "What did un- do here?",
      "kind": "guide",
      "path": "/audio/narration/guide-514d8c08.m4a"
    },
    {
      "id": "guide-2bc528b6",
      "text": "Make a word meaning not tidy.",
      "kind": "guide",
      "path": "/audio/narration/guide-2bc528b6.m4a"
    },
    {
      "id": "guide-b10a405d",
      "text": "Look at how the parts fit. Cover each word when you are ready.",
      "kind": "guide",
      "path": "/audio/narration/guide-b10a405d.m4a"
    },
    {
      "id": "guide-19b2add0",
      "text": "You discovered two jobs for un-. It can mean not, or reverse an action.",
      "kind": "guide",
      "path": "/audio/narration/guide-19b2add0.m4a"
    },
    {
      "id": "dictation-2da6379c",
      "text": "It was unfair to change the rules.",
      "kind": "dictation",
      "path": "/audio/narration/dictation-2da6379c.m4a"
    },
    {
      "id": "dictation-267cb964",
      "text": "It was unkind to leave her out.",
      "kind": "dictation",
      "path": "/audio/narration/dictation-267cb964.m4a"
    },
    {
      "id": "dictation-3d3f9e19",
      "text": "Please unlock the door before we leave.",
      "kind": "dictation",
      "path": "/audio/narration/dictation-3d3f9e19.m4a"
    },
    {
      "id": "dictation-d067abde",
      "text": "The untidy desk needed sorting.",
      "kind": "dictation",
      "path": "/audio/narration/dictation-d067abde.m4a"
    }
  ]
}
